## Naming Conventions

- **Files**: Use kebab-case for files (`user-profile.tsx`, `api-handler.ts`)
- **Components**: Use PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `NavigationBar`)
- **Functions/Variables**: Use camelCase (`getUserData`, `isLoading`)
- **Constants**: Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_RETRIES`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: Use PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `ApiResponse`)

## Indentation and Spacing

- Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- Use single quotes for strings (preferable) or double quotes (consistent)
- Add trailing commas in multi-line objects/arrays
- Use single empty line between logical sections
- Remove trailing whitespace

## TypeScript

- Always use TypeScript types, avoid `any`
- Use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/intersections
- Prefer `type` for utility types and complex types
- Use proper return types for functions
- Leverage TypeScript's type inference when appropriate

```typescript
// Good
interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

type UserStatus = 'active' | 'inactive' | 'pending';

function getUser(id: string): Promise<User> {
  // ...
}

// Avoid
function getUser(id: any): any {
  // ...
}
```

## Imports

- Group imports: external packages → internal modules → types
- Use absolute imports with path aliases when configured
- Remove unused imports
- Sort imports alphabetically within groups

```typescript
// Good
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { getUserData } from '@/lib/api';

import type { User } from '@/types/user';
```

## Comments

- Write self-documenting code (prefer clear names over comments)
- Use comments to explain "why", not "what"
- Use JSDoc comments for public functions/APIs
- Remove commented-out code before committing

## ESLint and Prettier

- Use ESLint for code quality
- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Ensure both are configured and run on save
- Fix linting errors before committing
- Use `.eslintrc.json` and `.prettierrc` for configuration

## File Organization

- One component per file
- Co-locate related files (component + styles + tests)
- Group related functionality in folders
- Use index files for clean imports when appropriate

## Code Quality

- Keep functions small and focused (single responsibility)
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3-4 levels)
- Extract magic numbers and strings into constants
- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- Prefer composition over inheritance
